                        data-uotrack="UtilityBarPrintBtn"
                        data-module-name="utility-bar-module-print"></div></div></div></div></div><section id="module-position-SnebHhg4lFw" class="storytopbar-bucket asset-nav-bar-module story-asset-nav-bar-module"></section><section id="module-position-SnebHhhKEuY" class="storytopbar-bucket story-headline-module story-story-headline-module"><h1 class="asset-headline speakable-headline" itemprop="headline">Memorable Lions moments online: Detroit&#39;s stars bring plenty of thrills, few playoff wins</h1></section><section id="module-position-SnebHhgAonc" class="storytopbar-bucket priority-asset-module story-priority-asset-module"></section><section id="module-position-SnebHhhYJDo" class="storytopbar-bucket story-byline-module story-story-byline-module"><div class="asset-metabar"><span class="asset-metabar-author asset-metabar-item" data-track-label="article|sports:nfl:lions|authorbyline"><a rel="author" href="http://www.detroitnews.com/staff/2647399001/john-niyo/">John Niyo</a>, The Detroit News</span><span class="asset-metabar-time asset-metabar-item nobyline">
            Published 2:39 p.m. ET April 8, 2020 | <span class="asset-metabar-time-updated">Updated 2:40 p.m. ET April 8, 2020</span></span></div></section><section id="module-position-SnebHhhSgQQ" class="storytopbar-bucket piano-module story-piano-module"></section><section id="module-position-SnebHhg8ypA" class="storytopbar-bucket bounce-exchange-module story-bounce-exchange-module"></section><div class="asset-double-wide double-wide p402_premium" role="main" itemprop="articleBody"><div id="module-position-SnebHnDAYyY" class="story-asset story-metadata-asset"></div><div id="module-position-SnebHnDE-9U" class="story-asset inline-share-tools-asset"><div class="inline-share-tools asset-inline-share-tools asset-inline-share-tools-top"><span
        class="inline-share-btn inline-share-btn-facebook"
        data-share-method="facebook"
        data-uotrack="InlineShareFacebookBtn"><span class="inline-share-count inline-share-count-facebook"></span><span class="inline-share-btn-label inline-share-btn-label-facebook">CONNECT</span></span><a
        class="inline-share-btn inline-share-btn-twitter"
        data-share-method="twitter"
        data-uotrack="InlineShareTwitterLink"
        data-popup-width="550"
        data-popup-height="450"
        href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https%3A//www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2020/04/08/memorable-detroit-lions-moments-online-more-thrills-than-victories/2970442001/&amp;text=Memorable%20Lions%20moments%20online%3A%20Detroit%27s%20stars%20bring%20plenty%20of%20thrills%2C%20few%20playoff%20wins&amp;via=detroitnews"
        target="_blank" data-popup
        rel="nofollow"><span class="inline-share-count inline-share-count-twitter"></span><span class="inline-share-btn-label inline-share-btn-label-twitter">TWEET</span></a><a
        class="inline-share-btn inline-share-btn-linkedin"
        data-share-method="linkedin"
        data-popup-width="600"
        data-popup-height="455"
        data-uotrack="UtilityBarFlyoutLinkedInLink"
        href="http://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?url=https%3A//www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2020/04/08/memorable-detroit-lions-moments-online-more-thrills-than-victories/2970442001/&amp;mini=true"
        target="_blank" data-popup
        rel="nofollow"><span class="inline-share-count inline-share-count-linkedin"></span><span class="inline-share-btn-label inline-share-btn-label-linkedin">LINKEDIN</span></a><span
            class="inline-share-btn inline-share-btn-comments"
            data-share-method="comments"
            data-uotrack="InlineShareCommentsBtn"><span class="inline-share-count inline-share-count-comments"></span><span class="inline-share-btn-label inline-share-btn-label-comments">COMMENT</span></span><span
        class="inline-share-btn inline-share-btn-email"
        data-share-method="email"
        data-uotrack="InlineShareEmailBtn"><span class="inline-share-count inline-share-count-email"></span><span class="inline-share-btn-label inline-share-btn-label-email">EMAIL</span></span><span
         class="inline-share-btn inline-share-btn-more"
         data-share-method="facebook"
         data-uotrack="InlineShareMoreBtn"><span class="inline-share-count inline-share-count-more"></span><span class="inline-share-btn-label inline-share-btn-label-more">MORE</span></span></div></div><p class="speakable-p-1 p-text">In the absence of live sports, TV networks are filling airtime by replaying classic games from the past, some involving our local teams. But if you need a stronger dose of Detroit-area sports to tide you over until the games begin again, we&rsquo;ve come up with a list you can find online.</p><p class="speakable-p-2 p-text">The NFL just made things easier for fans by making a decade&rsquo;s worth of games available for free on Gamepass via NFL.com. Recent Major League Baseball games are relatively easy to find on YouTube. But same goes for other sports, and we&rsquo;ve compiled a list of 10 memorable games from each of our four major pro franchise, as well as Michigan and Michigan State football and basketball.</p><p class="p-text">Today, it&rsquo;s the Lions, who&rsquo;ve had their share of thrilling moments, even if most of their playoff success was broadcast in black-and-white:</p><p class="p-text">► <a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UKfUCtMOjm4" target="_blank">Dec. 27, 1953 &mdash;&nbsp;Lions 17, Browns 16:</a> The Lions, led by Bobby Layne and Doak Walker, won the second of three consecutive NFL championship game matchups with the Cleveland Browns, rallying in the fourth quarter to defend their title at Briggs Stadium.</p><div id="module-position-SnebHnCuTM4" class="story-asset image-asset"><aside itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" class="wide single-photo"><img itemprop="url" src="https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2020/04/08/PDTN/82d25899-2ebf-4b51-a8ce-656338b188e6-rote.jpg?width=540&amp;height=&amp;fit=bounds&amp;auto=webp" alt="Lions quarterback Tobin Rote runs into the end zone for a touchdown in the 1957 championship game." width="540" data-mycapture-src="https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2020/04/08/PDTN/82d25899-2ebf-4b51-a8ce-656338b188e6-rote.jpg"
                    data-mycapture-sm-src="https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2020/04/08/PDTN/82d25899-2ebf-4b51-a8ce-656338b188e6-rote.jpg" /><meta itemprop="name" content="Rote" /><meta itemprop="height" content="405" /><meta itemprop="width" content="540" /><p>Lions quarterback Tobin Rote runs into the end zone for a touchdown in the 1957 championship game.<meta itemprop="copyrightHolder" content="Detroit News archives" />&nbsp;<span class="credit">(Photo: Detroit News archives)</span></p></aside><div class="clearfix"></div></div><p class="p-text">► <strong>Dec. 29, 1957 &mdash;&nbsp;Lions 59, Browns 14:</strong> Savor this one, because who knows when you&rsquo;ll ever see another Lions team win a title. With Tobin Rote filling in for an injured Bobby Lane, the underdogs from Detroit routed the Cleveland Browns &mdash;&nbsp;and rookie running back Jim Brown &mdash;&nbsp;in the 1957 NFL Championship Game at Briggs Stadium.</p><p class="p-text"><a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rdKjyFF2LVA" target="_blank">Part 1</a></p><p class="p-text"><a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PAKQ_KO9Uac" target="_blank">Part 2</a></p><p class="p-text">► <a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9aMMWVBGUws" target="_blank">Nov. 22, 1962 &mdash;&nbsp;Lions 26, Packers 14: </a>This one is remembered as the Thanksgiving Massacre, as the Lions gained revenge for an earlier heartbreak and spoiled the Packers&rsquo; perfect season, sacking Bart Starr 11 times at Tiger Stadium.</p><div class="partner-placement partner-spike" data-ad-placement="native-article_link" data-ad-sizes='["fluid",[3,3], [2,6]]'></div><p class="p-text">► <a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kF9yKEuG4kM" target="_blank">Nov. 24, 1991 &mdash;&nbsp;Lions 34, Vikings 14: </a>A week after Mike Utley suffered a neck injury that left him paralyzed from the neck down, an inspired Lions team routed the Vikings at the Metrodome behind Barry Sanders&rsquo; franchise-record 220 yards rushing and four touchdowns. Thumbs up.</p><p class="p-text">► <a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=soH33XuFUk0" target="_blank">Jan. 5, 1992 &mdash; Lions 38, Cowboys 6:</a> This was the Lions last playoff win, and it was a memorable one, as a roaring Silverdome crowd watched Detroit demolish the Dallas Cowboys, led by Erik Kramer&rsquo;s 341 passing yards and capped by one of Barry Sanders&rsquo; all-time best touchdown runs in the fourth quarter.</p><div id="module-position-SnebHnC8SqY" class="story-asset image-asset"><aside itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" class="single-photo float"><img itemprop="url" src="https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2020/04/08/PDTN/568341b2-d63b-47b1-822e-1b0d5dc2fd88-sanders.jpg?width=180&amp;height=240&amp;fit=bounds&amp;auto=webp" alt="Lions running back Barry Sanders broke the single-season 2,000-yard mark in this game in 1997 against the New York Jets." width="180" data-mycapture-src="https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2020/04/08/PDTN/568341b2-d63b-47b1-822e-1b0d5dc2fd88-sanders.jpg"
                    data-mycapture-sm-src="https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2020/04/08/PDTN/568341b2-d63b-47b1-822e-1b0d5dc2fd88-sanders.jpg" /><meta itemprop="name" content="Sanders Lyle" /><meta itemprop="height" content="240" /><meta itemprop="width" content="180" /><p>Lions running back Barry Sanders broke the single-season 2,000-yard mark in this game in 1997 against the New York Jets.<meta itemprop="copyrightHolder" content="Tom Pidgeon, Associated Press" />&nbsp;<span class="credit">(Photo: Tom Pidgeon, Associated Press)</span></p></aside></div><p class="p-text">► <a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mvaZxuDqs5s" target="_blank">Dec. 21, 1997 &mdash;&nbsp;Lions 13, Jets 10: </a>This was the game was an emotional roller coaster. Reggie Brown nearly died on the field, but the regular-season finale continued after a lengthy delay and Barry Sanders cracked the 2,000-yard mark and the Lions clinched a playoff berth.</p><div id="module-position-SnebHnCROGI" class="story-asset image-asset"><aside itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" class="single-photo float"><img itemprop="url" src="https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2020/04/08/PDTN/d1d81a92-77eb-4e7d-a25c-6c09da56b17e-staffordhurt.jpg?width=180&amp;height=240&amp;fit=bounds&amp;auto=webp" alt="Quarterback Matthew Stafford led the Lions to a last-second victory over the Browns in 2011, despite injuring his shoulder here in the fourth quarter." width="180" data-mycapture-src="https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2020/04/08/PDTN/d1d81a92-77eb-4e7d-a25c-6c09da56b17e-staffordhurt.jpg"
                    data-mycapture-sm-src="https://www.gannett-cdn.com/presto/2020/04/08/PDTN/d1d81a92-77eb-4e7d-a25c-6c09da56b17e-staffordhurt.jpg" /><meta itemprop="name" content="Staffordhurt" /><meta itemprop="height" content="240" /><meta itemprop="width" content="180" /><p>Quarterback Matthew Stafford led the Lions to a last-second victory over the Browns in 2011, despite injuring his shoulder here in the fourth quarter.<meta itemprop="copyrightHolder" content="Robin Buckson, Detroit News" />&nbsp;<span class="credit">(Photo: Robin Buckson, Detroit News)</span></p></aside></div><p class="p-text">► <a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KvzmwPIsQGU" target="_blank">Nov. 22, 2009 &mdash;&nbsp;Lions 38, Browns 37: </a>Matthew Stafford made believers of his teammates &mdash;&nbsp;and a lot of Lions fans &mdash;&nbsp;with this record-setting performance for a rookie, shaking off a separated shoulder on the game-winning drive in dramatic fashion.&nbsp;</p><p class="p-text">► <a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://gamepass.nfl.com/game/bears-at-lions-on-10102011" target="_blank">Oct. 10, 2011 &mdash;&nbsp;Lions 24, Bears 13:</a> Detroit was on Monday Night Football for the first time in a decade, and Ford Field was ready. So were the undefeated Lions, who used big plays from Calvin Johnson and Jahvid Best &mdash;&nbsp;remember him? &mdash;&nbsp;to snap a six-game losing streak to the Bears</p><div class="partner-placement partner-spike" data-ad-placement="native-article_link" data-ad-sizes='["fluid",[3,3], [2,6]]'></div><p class="p-text">► <a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f24bwtXDEwk" target="_blank">Dec. 24, 2011 &mdash;&nbsp;Lions 38, Chargers 10:</a> Christmas came early for Lions fans, as the home team clinched their first playoff berth of the millennium and celebrated by taking a victory lap at Ford Field, high-fiving fans.</p><p class="p-text">► <a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z3Qze5ICz8g" target="_blank">Oct. 27, 2013 &mdash;&nbsp;Lions 31, Cowboys 30:</a> Matthew Stafford threw for 488 yards and Calvin Johnson set an NFL record for a regulation game with 14 catches for 329 yards in a game that ended with Stafford faking a spike and diving into the end zone for the tying touchdown.</p><cta-atoms-container-inline></cta-atoms-container-inline><p class="p-text"><em>jniyo@detroitnews.com</em></p><p class="p-text"><em>Twitter: @JohnNiyo</em></p><h3 class="presto-h3"><strong>Previous installments</strong></h3><p class="p-text"><a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/nba/pistons/2020/04/07/memorable-detroit-pistons-moments-online-nba-crowns-palace-chaos/2962407001/" target="_blank">Memorable Pistons moments online: From NBA crowns to Palace chaos</a></p><p class="p-text"><a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/nhl/red-wings/2020/04/05/watch-memorable-red-wings-games-1950-2008-stanley-cup-clinchers-among-10-extraordinary-contests/2951050001/" target="_blank">Memorable Red Wings moments online:&nbsp;1950, 2008 Stanley Cup clinchers among 10 extraordinary&nbsp;contests</a></p><p class="p-text p-text-last"id="article-body-p-last"><a data-track-label="inline|intext|n/a" href="https://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/mlb/tigers/2020/04/06/memorable-tigers-moments-online-series-heroes-jvs-no-nos-galarragas-close-call/2954126001/" target="_blank">Memorable Tigers moments online: Series heroes, JV&#39;s no-nos, Galarraga&#39;s close call</a></p><div id="module-position-SnebHnCKqJA" class="story-asset inline-share-tools-asset"><div class="inline-share-tools asset-inline-share-tools asset-inline-share-tools-bottom"><span
